5. `\maketitle`: This command generates the title page.
6. `\tableofcontents`: This command generates the table of contents automatically based on the chapters and sections in the document.
7. `\mainmatter`: This command starts the main matter of the document, which includes the chapters.
8. `\chapter{...}`: This command starts a new chapter.
9. `\section{...}`: This command starts a new section within a chapter.

When you compile this LaTeX document, it will generate a table of contents that lists all the chapters and sections in the document.

